					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>An anonymous commentary on the book of Leviticus (fragments).</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="jrb-Hebr" otherLangs="he">Judeo-Arabic, Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="186v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש ויקרא</title>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush va-yikra'</title>
							<note>
								<p>Part of an Arabic commentary on Leviticus, chapters 11:1 to 15:25.</p>
								<p>Some parts of the commentary begin with a short introduction and a doxology.</p>
								<p>The only Karaite authority mentioned by name is Anan (e.g. folio 182r). The Rabbanites are quoted in various places in the text (e.g. folios 14v, 19r, 41v, 72v, 74r, 181r), and Al-Fayyumi is cited by name in various chapters (e.g. folios 17v, 19r, 26v, 45r, 46v, 47r, 163r, 177r, 181r). </p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Cf. contents of Or 2561, <ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">305</ref>
							</filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 13th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex.</support>
								<extent>186 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>180</height>
										<width>145</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>145</height>
										<width>105</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>186 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Originally quires of mostly 10 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Catchwords at the end of the quires. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>Lacunae after folios: 12, 21, 31, 45, 48, 61, 115.<p>Imperfect at the beginning and at the end.</p>
									<p>Many folios worm-eaten and/or damaged.</p>
									<p>Stained.</p>
									<p>Worming with some loss of text. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
